    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen launching treesitter from an autocommand and then, later in the config file, enabling syntax and filetype plugin/indent, the BufReadPost and BufRead events will not be triggered for files that:\r\n1. Also launch treesitter.\r\n2. Are loaded in as CLI options.\r\n\r\nFor whatever reason, this only happens if the file does `syntax enable` before it does `filetype plugin indent on`\r\n\r\nIf `syntax enable` or the treesitter autocommand are removed, the BufReadPost event triggers as expected.\r\n\r\nExample configuration that has this issue:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal augroup = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup\r\nlocal autocmd = vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd\r\n\r\naugroup('VimrcAutoCommands', { clear = true })\r\n\r\nautocmd('FileType', {\r\n    group = 'VimrcAutoCommands',\r\n    pattern = 'c,vim,vimdoc,lua,query',\r\n    callback = function(args) vim.treesitter.start(args.buf, args.match) end\r\n})\r\n\r\nautocmd('BufReadPost', { group = 'VimrcAutoCommands', pattern = '*',\r\n    callback = function(args)  vim.opt.number = true end\r\n})\r\n\r\nvim.cmd([[\r\n    syntax enable\r\n    filetype plugin indent on\r\n]])\r\n```\r\nWhen using the above configuration with a supported file type, line numbers are not displayed.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim ~/.config/nvim/init.lua\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nUsing the provided configuration file, line numbers should be enabled when viewing init.lua.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo (Vim does not have treesitter)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 22.04 (WSL)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nST 0.9 + Tmux 3.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
